Male genitalia. Abdominal segment IX with medial acuminate keel dorsally and setae covering right and left sides (dorsal view) (
Fig. 2E
); anterior margins sinuous; posterior margins sinuous, covered by setae, and each side with one deep notch (lateral view) (
Fig. 2B
). Segment X bilobed with wart on rounded apex of each lobe (dorsal view) (
Fig. 2E
); subtriangular and apically rounded, with two transverse rows of setae near nid-length (lateral view) (
Fig. 2B
). Inferior appendages almost uniformly wide, covered by small setae throughout their length and longer setae on dorsal surfaces; each with basal segment two to three times length of apical segment. Phallus arched; apex subtruncate (lateral view) (
Fig. 2C
); phallotremal sclerite without dorsal process; anterior margin concave and posterior margin bearing pair of large rounded prominences (ventral view) (
Fig. 2D
); phallotrema rounded, concave, apically positioned on posterior surface of phallus (
Fig. 2C
).
